5.0 out of 5 stars If you are considering a SMALL..
Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2014
Verified Purchase
Okay, I'm 5'4, 105lbs, 33/26/33, c-cup. Very very tiny. Like, people ask me "if I eat" on a daily basis, lol, So ya, Im a small if u ever did see one. I went by their size chart under the description and the small was the closest fit. When it gets here, I could barely put it on. I mean, I physically could, had I not any need to breathe, eat, or bend over. And there had to be at least 1 inch of an opening in the back to be even remotely comfortable. And I also noticed that due to my chest size (thanks mom$$ lol) it no longer resembled a sweetheart neckline... It was more straight across. My boobs were literally suffocating. The small is definitely not for anyone any larger than an A cup. It was pretty obvious the small did not fit me. The only people I could see fitting into a small would be the extra teeny tiny, small breasted, small framed, on the shorter side, Asian ladies like you would see at the nail salon. After all, these are Asian sizes. Not trying to be funny, I'm trying to help someone decide which size they should buy.

So I reordered a medium. The medium got here today, and I could not be more happy. :) It fits like a glove and I do not even have to unlace it, which is ideal for me. Their size chart seems to be off a few centimeters, although I can promise you, once on, the waist is exact. The medium is exactly 67 centis and the small is 63 (when laced closed). The seller gave me a refund on the small, so I'm happy.

FYI, the got the Victorian style, As well, and the small fits but is actually kinda large on me in the bust, lol, go figure... Still wearable though, just need a padded strapless. So they are two very diff sizes, and it's hard to tell Bc the Victorian doesn't have a size chart on the page, except amazons standard.. Which clearly isn't close to correct with these. And of course, before it got here, I had reordered that one in medium, too, based on how THIS small fit. Big mistake. The small came like a day after I reordered it in medium, and like I said fit pretty well. So now I have an extra Victorian style too. As well as this in a small that I can't wear either. But szivyshi and Surenow (the two sellers I bought from) both refunded me so it's fine. Don't get me wrong, once you find the correct size, these are sooooo worth the money and are very well made, The corsets are awesome. Very pretty and elegant.. without looking like a sex worker.

Another update 10/8/14:
My mom liked it so much she wanted one, so I took her measurements and the closest was for 4x.. And she's not even remotely overweight. She weights about 140, wears a 38D/DD, ~38" hips, but carries some weight and her stomach area.. So her waiste is ~42". The 4X fit like a charm. She has an abdominal hernia so it was obviously tight around the waist but we were able to get it closed and it was cute, I haven't seen her face light up like that in years. she looked pretty lovely and she's 60! The one thing is, she had a hard time arranging her breasts in the bust area because they aren't as perky as they used to be. So if gravity has moderately affected your breasts, you may want to consider wearing a strapless bra with this. Not a big deal. So yeah, like I said, once you find the right size, it's really a very pretty corset. I promise you will not look like a dominatrix.. Lol unless you match this with fishnets and a crotchless thong.. But hey, I don't judge :)
